abstract: Prosecutors say the man posted violent threats on Gab, a social media app popular with the far right.
snippet: Prosecutors say the man posted violent threats on Gab, a social media app popular with the far right.
lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors charged a Pennsylvania man on Monday with posting multiple violent threats against the F.B.I. online in the days that followed the bureau’s search of former President Donald J. Trump’s private club and residence in Florida.

main: Pennsylvania Man Charged With Threatening F.B.I. After Mar-a-Lago Search

abstract: The tech giant is sprinting to protect its core business with a flurry of projects, including updates to its search engine and plans for an all-new one.
snippet: The tech giant is sprinting to protect its core business with a flurry of projects, including updates to its search engine and plans for an all-new one.
lead_paragraph: Google’s employees were shocked when they learned in March that the South Korean consumer electronics giant Samsung was considering replacing Google with Microsoft’s Bing as the default search engine on its devices.

main: Google Devising Radical Search Changes to Beat Back A.I. Rivals
print_headline: Google’s Fight To Stay Ahead Of Bing’s A.I.

abstract: Dmitri A. Muratov, whose newspaper was shuttered in response to the Kremlin’s increasingly draconian censorship, will donate the proceeds to Ukrainian refugees.
snippet: Dmitri A. Muratov, whose newspaper was shuttered in response to the Kremlin’s increasingly draconian censorship, will donate the proceeds to Ukrainian refugees.
lead_paragraph: After winning the Nobel Peace Prize last October, the Russian journalist Dmitri A. Muratov said he thought the honor should have gone to a different Russian: the jailed opposition leader Aleksei A. Navalny.

main: Russian Journalist to Auction Nobel Medal to Benefit Ukraine
print_headline: Russian  Journalist To Auction His Nobel

abstract: The Justice Department’s antitrust lawsuit, which a group of states joined, was the fifth by U.S. officials against the company since 2020.
snippet: The Justice Department’s antitrust lawsuit, which a group of states joined, was the fifth by U.S. officials against the company since 2020.
lead_paragraph: The Justice Department and a group of eight states sued Google on Tuesday, accusing it of illegally abusing a monopoly over the technology that powers online advertising, in the agency’s first antitrust lawsuit against a tech giant under President Biden and an escalation in legal pressure on one of the world’s biggest internet companies.

main: U.S. Accuses Google of Abusing Monopoly in Ad Technology
print_headline: U.S. Accuses Google of Abusing Its Monopoly

original: By David McCabe and Nico Grant

abstract: Wagner’s reach extends far beyond the war in Ukraine.
snippet: Wagner’s reach extends far beyond the war in Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: One of the groups that have risen to international prominence (or infamy) with the invasion of Ukraine is Wagner, a Kremlin-backed mercenary outfit that regularly employs former criminals. In Ukraine, they often fight when conventional Russian Army troops flee the battlefield, and they are noted for their brutality.

abstract: The president says oil is his economy’s worst addiction. Phasing it out would be a global first for a major oil producer.
snippet: The president says oil is his economy’s worst addiction. Phasing it out would be a global first for a major oil producer.
lead_paragraph: ARAUCA, Colombia — Over the past four decades, Colombia has pumped billions of barrels of oil from under a vast savanna it shares with neighboring Venezuela. Through pipelines, the thick crude travels over the Andes and to the Caribbean coast, and then onto tankers, mostly to the United States.

main: In Colombia, Drilling Pays the Bills. The Country’s Leaders Want to Quit Oil.
print_headline: Colombia Depends on Oil. Its Leader Wants to Give It Up.

original: By Max Bearak and Federico Rios

abstract: The Biden administration has charted the same course as the Trump administration on strategic priorities like China, the Middle East and U.S. military deployments.
snippet: The Biden administration has charted the same course as the Trump administration on strategic priorities like China, the Middle East and U.S. military deployments.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A fist bump and meeting with the crown prince of Saudi Arabia. Tariffs and export controls on China. Jerusalem as the capital of Israel. American troops out of Afghanistan.

main: On U.S. Foreign Policy, the New Boss Acts a Lot Like the Old One
print_headline: Biden Is Charting a Similar Course to Trump on U.S. Foreign Policy

abstract: The president’s plan focuses on less affluent student borrowers.
snippet: The president’s plan focuses on less affluent student borrowers.
lead_paragraph: Fewer than 40 percent of Americans graduate from a four-year college, and these college graduates fare far better than nongraduates on a wide range of measures. College graduates earn much more on average; are less likely to endure unemployment; are more likely to marry; are healthier; live longer; and express greater satisfaction with their lives. These gaps have generally grown in recent decades.

abstract: Newly mobilized recruits are already at the front in Ukraine, a growing chorus of reports says, fighting and dying after only days of training.
snippet: Newly mobilized recruits are already at the front in Ukraine, a growing chorus of reports says, fighting and dying after only days of training.
lead_paragraph: A half-dozen Russian soldiers talk about being shipped to an area of intense fighting in eastern Ukraine just 11 days after their mobilization. Asked about his shooting practice, a bearded conscript says, “Once. Three magazines.”

main: ‘Coffins Are Already Coming’: The Toll of Russia’s Chaotic Draft
print_headline: Inside Russia’s Chaotic Draft, Desperation Swells

abstract: Leaders from both parties have reached an agreement.
snippet: Leaders from both parties have reached an agreement.
